<HEADLINE>
<P>
READERS TOUCH ALL BASES ON TOUCHY ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Who the heck is Mike Downey to preach to me? 
</P>
<P>
His column, "Remember, This Isn't a Show, It Doesn't Have to Go On," was more 
suited for a soapbox or pulpit than the sports section. 
</P>
<P>
I always thought that sportswriters were frustrated jocks. Now I know some are 
frustrated philosophers. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN CUSUMANO, Chatsworth 
</P>
</TEXT>
