<HEADLINE>
<P>
READERS TOUCH ALL BASES ON TOUCHY ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How can human beings guzzle beer, cheer wildly, do high-fives and celebrate 
five miles away from a scene where they were digging for bodies of earthquake 
victims? 
</P>
<P>
Perhaps the loss of huge revenues by the networks, advertisers, media, fans et 
al is more precious to some than the human lives and misery that prevails at 
this time. 
</P>
<P>
You wonder how far we have come since Nero fiddled while Rome burned. 
</P>
<P>
BLYDEN BOYLE, Pacific Palisades 
</P>
</TEXT>
