<HEADLINE>
<P>
READERS TOUCH ALL BASES ON TOUCHY ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If Mike Downey really feels there ought to be some respect shown for the Bay 
Area's dead, he shouldn't be urging that we cancel the World Series. 
</P>
<P>
He should launch a campaign to shut down Universal Studios' earthquake 
attraction. I noted with disgust that although Universal temporarily closed the 
"ride," they reopened it in time for the weekend crowds. Money talks, as usual. 
</P>
<P>
Earthquakes are not a joke. They shouldn't be portrayed as thrill rides. Get 
serious, Southern California -- you're next. 
</P>
<P>
GLENN KRELL, San Francisco 
</P>
