<HEADLINE>
<P>
READERS TOUCH ALL BASES ON TOUCHY ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What a glaring difference between the two columns the day after the earthquake. 
Jim Murray's was measured, compassionate and insightful. Mike Downey's 
hysterical and posturing. He writes: "Why the gods chose to strike down . . ." 
"Ours is not to reason why?" This guy would make Grantland Rice blush. 
</P>
<P>
Then Downey called for the World Series to be canceled. Nonsense. Human beings 
have a magnificent ability not only to survive but to prevail. The games will 
do more for morale than a million pious mumblings in newspaper columns. 
</P>
<P>
ED HONECK, Orange 
</P>
</TEXT>
