<HEADLINE>
<P>
NHL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
TURGEON PLAYS KEY ROLE IN SABRES' 6-5 WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN HAFNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pierre Turgeon assisted on the tying goal in the last minute of regulation 
Friday night at Buffalo, then scored at 2:30 of overtime to give the Sabres a 
6-5 victory over the Toronto Maple Leafs. 
</P>
<P>
The Sabres gave up four goals in the first eight minutes and still trailed by 
three goals going into the last period. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Foligno scored early in the third period, but only 3:18 remained in 
regulation when Rick Vaive brought the Sabres within one. Foligno's second goal 
of the period at 19:01 sent the game into overtime. 
</P>
<P>
New York Islanders 5, New York Rangers 5 -- With a three-goal lead going into 
the final period, the Islanders were in a strong position to hand the Rangers 
their first loss at home this season. 
</P>
<P>
But the Rangers rallied to get the tie and are 4-0-3 on home ice. 
</P>
<P>
In 2 1/2 minutes, the Rangers had goals from Carey Wilson and Tomas Sandstrom, 
and with 5:34 left, rookie defenseman Miljoslav Horava tied it with his first 
NHL goal. 
</P>
<P>
Vancouver 5, Calgary 5 -- The Flames needed goals by Sergei Makarov and Theoren 
Fleury in the final five minutes of regulation at Calgary to get the tie. 
</P>
<P>
Fleury's tying goal came with only three seconds left. DAN HAFNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
