<HEADLINE>
<P>
CS LONG BEACH FACES OREGON AT EUGENE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DICK WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EUGENE, Ore. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach's football team, which lost to Oregon here last season, 
49-0, will have a nonconference rematch with the Ducks at 1 p.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
"We remembered what happened last year and hopefully that will be motivation 
enough," said Long Beach Coach Larry Reisbig. 
</P>
<P>
The 49ers, who lost to San Jose State last week, 21-10, are 3-5 overall and 1-3 
in the Big West Conference. They have defeated only one Division I-A team, 
winless New Mexico State. 
</P>
<P>
Oregon (4-3) is led by quarterback Bill Musgrave and tailback Derek Loville, 
neither of whom the 49ers could stop a year ago. In that game, Loville ran for 
154 yards and Musgrave threw three touchdown passes. 
</P>
<P>
Loville had a 203-yard game last week as the Ducks defeated Arizona State, 
27-7. DICK WAGNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
