<HEADLINE>
<P>
BAY AREA QUAKE AFTERMATH AND FREEWAY SAFETY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How do we pay for the terrible destruction done by Hurricane Hugo and the San 
Francisco earthquake? I believe two or three Stealth bombers would do it. We 
could use the money to rebuild, the engineers could be put to work designing 
stronger structures and roads and designing a workable rapid transit system for 
big cities. Workers could be given jobs rebuilding cities instead of building 
bombs. 
</P>
<P>
When we finish that, the money could be used for schools. One bomber could 
probably solve the overcrowding in the area that I teach in. Building schools, 
furnishing them and staffing them could create many jobs as well as filling a 
vital need. 
</P>
<P>
We don't need to raise taxes -- we just need to change our priorities! 
</P>
<P>
ELAINE BUDIN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
