<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CHANNEL LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG MEADE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oxnard 32, Rio Mesa 22 -- Fullback Bryant Taylor rushed for 223 yards and 
scored the game's first and last touchdowns to lead the Yellowjackets at Rio 
Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
Rio Mesa closed to within three points with 5:15 remaining on a 13-yard 
touchdown pass from Henry Wilson to Charles Thompson, but Taylor answered with 
a 49-yard scoring run to put the game out of reach. Gordy Abellera of Rio Mesa 
(4-4, 2-3) rushed 14 times for 51 yards, including a 24-yard touchdown run. 
GREG MEADE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
