<P>
IN OTHER VALLEY PAC-8 CONFERENCE GAMES: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TODD JACOBSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sylmar 20, Van Nuys 3 -- Jerome Casey rushed for 89 yards in 13 carries and 
scored two touchdowns to lead the Spartans (4-2, 2-2) at Sylmar. 
</P>
<P>
Casey put Sylmar ahead in the second quarter, 7-3, on a 27-yard touchdown pass 
from Daniel Terry. The Spartans increased the lead to 13-3 when Daniel Moreno, 
the holder on kicks, connected on a 20-yard scoring pass to Girmar Johnson on a 
fake field-goal play. 
</P>
<P>
Casey capped the scoring with a 28-yard touchdown run in the fourth quarter. 
Van Nuys running back Aaron Gadasy rushed for 89 yards in 26 carries. TODD 
JACOBSON 
