<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARVARD CLAIMS WATER POLO PLAYOFF BERTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harvard High clinched its first Southern Section 3-A Division playoff berth in 
water polo with an 11-7 victory Friday over Mater Dei in a Del Rey League match 
at Mater Dei High. 
</P>
<P>
Freshman Jim Toring had four goals and teammate Eric Deutsch added three for 
the Saracens (24-4 overall, 9-0 in league play), who are ranked fourth in the 
division. Goalie Antonio Gomez recorded eight saves. 
</P>
<P>
Although Mater Dei (6-4 in league play) scored first, Harvard led, 7-2, at 
intermission and the outcome was never in question. "Even when they were ahead 
it wasn't close," Harvard Coach Rich Corso quipped. 
</P>
<P>
But Corso, whose team moved up from the 2-A Division this season, has his 
sights on more than a league title. 
</P>
<P>
"League wins are fine but what we're really pointing toward is 12 days from 
now," he said, referring to the opening playoff match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
