<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FREE FLU SHOTS OFFERED TO RESIDENTS OVER 55 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Department of Health Services is offering free flu shots 
to county residents 55 and older through Dec. 15. 
</P>
<P>
The shots will be offered through local senior citizens centers and county 
health centers and clinics. 
</P>
<P>
Dr. Stephen H. Waterman, the county's chief of Acute Communicable Disease 
Control, recommended the shots to senior citizens and younger people who have 
heart and lung conditions. 
</P>
<P>
Waterman said that people who receive the shots could still contract the flu, 
but symptoms would be milder. 
</P>
<P>
The health department also recommends that people over 65 receive pneumococcal 
immunizations, of which only one is needed in a lifetime. Senior citizens are 
advised to check with the health department to find the location of the nearest 
clinic offering those immunizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
