<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FHA Loan Ceiling Bill Passes: In an 84-6 vote, the Senate approved legislation 
raising to $124,875 the ceiling on home mortgages insured by the federal 
government in high-cost housing markets. The measure, part of a $67-billion 
spending bill, now goes to President Bush for approval. Currently, the ceiling 
on mortgages insured by the Federal Housing Administration is $101,250, an 
amount below the median price of homes in the District of Columbia and 18 
states, including California. 
</P>
