</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Treasury Changes a Date: The Treasury announced that it is amending next week's 
13-week and 26-week Treasury bill auction, pushing up the issue date from 
Thursday to Tuesday. The auctions will each be for $7.8 billion in securities 
and will be held Monday. The Treasury also announced an auction on Monday for 
$2 billion in 51-day cash management bills; the bills will have a Tuesday 
issuance date. The changes were made so that the Treasury could borrow the 
funds in advance of Oct. 31, when a temporary federal debt ceiling of $2.87 
trillion expires and the ceiling reverts back to the permanent level of $2.8 
trillion. 
