<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SACRAMENTO; 
</P>
<P>
AMANDA BLAKE'S KIN CHALLENGE HER WILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Relatives of the late actress Amanda Blake claim that the owner of a south 
Sacramento County animal preserve coerced her into leaving her entire estate to 
the refuge. Blake's mother, sister and two cousins filed suit in Sacramento 
Superior Court this week, contending that the actress actually wanted to leave 
her estate to them. The suit said she was talked into leaving it to the 
Performing Animal Welfare Society three days before she died at age 60 in a 
Sacramento hospital on Aug. 16. Blake played Miss Kitty on television's 
"Gunsmoke." 
</P>
</TEXT>
