<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
FRESNO COUNTY; 
</P>
<P>
LETTUCE WORKERS STRIKE OVER WAGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 3,000 lettuce workers have gone on strike after rejecting a three-year 
contract providing an 8-cent hourly wage hike from grower Bud Antle Inc. The 
workers walked off fields in Huron, Salinas and Santa Maria on Thursday, 10 
days into the fall harvest at the Huron site. The lettuce will blossom and turn 
to seed if it is not harvested in four or five days, according to the Fresno 
County Agriculture Department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
