<HEADLINE>
<P>
GAGAU SCORES TWO TOUCHDOWNS IN LA QUINTA ROUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
La Quinta High School kept its playoff hopes alive Friday night, trouncing 
Santiago, 34-0, before a homecoming crowd at Bolsa Grande. 
</P>
<P>
Keeping with a "Looney Tunes" homecoming theme, the Aztecs (4-4, 3-2) dropped a 
refrigerator on the Cavaliers (2-6, 1-4) as 6-foot-3, 318-pound Sunny Gagau 
scored two touchdowns to help keep La Quinta tied for third in the Garden Grove 
league. 
</P>
<P>
Gagau's first score came early in the second quarter when he scooped up a 
Cavalier fumble and then ran 55 yards for a touchdown giving La Quinta a 20-0 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
On La Quinta's next possession, after moving to the Santiago 12, La Quinta 
Coach Roger Takahashi put Gagau into the backfield where he passed to Walter 
Dawkins off a halfback option play to extend the lead to 27-0. 
</P>
<P>
"Sunny is a great athlete," Takahashi said, "it was just a little twist off the 
pitch play." MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA102889-0130 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 127052 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
