<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ORANGE COAST CLINCHES WATER POLO TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tony Litwak scored seven goals to lead Orange Coast College to a 12-7 victory 
over San Diego Mesa Friday, clinching the Orange Empire Conference water polo 
title at San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
Brian Oylear had 13 saves for OCC (22-4 overall and 10-0 in conference play). 
OCC's title is its first in three seasons. 
</P>
<P>
In another Orange Empire Conference water polo match: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 7, Rancho Santiago 5 -- Craig Shimomura had three goals and Craig 
Garcia added two for host Cypress (20-8, 7-4). The victory marked the first 
time Cypress had won at least 20 matches since 1973. Rancho Santiago is 8-15, 
0-11. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange Empire Conference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast 3, Fullerton 2 -- Oldham scored two goals in the first half and 
Andy Strouse scored in second half as OCC (11-3-2, 5-0-1) opened a 3-0 lead. 
Fullerton (10-7-1, 3-3) made it close on late second-half goals by Bill Saba 
and J.R. Ochs. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 2, Golden West 1 -- Manny Diaz scored late in the first half to break a 
1-1 tie for Cypress (4-9-3, 1-4-1) in the first half. Diego Abbes scored 
Cypress' other goal. Craig Larson scored for Golden West (1-12-2, 0-4-2). 
</P>
<P>
In South Coast Conference women's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 5, Oxnard 0 -- Deena Haurer scored two goals, Kristin Dailey, 
Leanna Jay and Kerry Kelter had one each for host Golden West (7-5-4, 6-3-1). 
</P>
</TEXT>
