<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UCI MEN BEAT USC SWIMMERS FOR FIRST TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brian Judd won the 200- and 500-yard freestyle events, and Brian Pajer won the 
100- and 200-yard breaststroke races to lead the UC Irvine men's swimming team 
to a 75-47 season-opening victory over USC at Heritage Park on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
It was Irvine's first victory against USC in men's swimming. 
</P>
<P>
Judd won the 200-yard freestyle in a time of one minute 44.83 seconds and the 
500 in 4:41.36. Pajer won the 100 breaststroke in 58:61 and the 200 in 2:11.43. 
</P>
<P>
Other double-winners for Irvine: Mat Curry won the 100 freestyle (47.95) and 
100 backstroke (54.83) and Jeff Klatt won the 100 (52.50) and 200 butterfly 
events (1:58.93). 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Conference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 3, Cal State Los Angeles 0 -- Host Chapman (24-2, 7-0) swept, 15-2, 
15-0, 15-6. Christy Anderson had nine kills and Rena Strange eight for Chapman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
